reviews.headline: Feels heavenly! (Rose Amber)
reviews.comments: While looking online I thought about ordering the Fenty Glow color. I have darker auburn hair with a light neutral/cool skin tone. But I went into the store and was able to test all the colors against my skin. I decided to buy the Rose Amber. Online that one looked too dark but the color is subtle and really pretty! Feels comfortable and hydrating. Nice shimmer, not too sparkly. Compared to Kylie's High Gloss, this is slightly less sticky feeling (smoother) and less pigmented. Both are great for different looks. Highly recommend.

reviews.headline: Not Sticky!
reviews.comments: This lip oil is amazing! It glides on smoothly, feels super lightweight, hydrates deeply, and leaves my lips glossy without being sticky.

reviews.headline: Gloss bomb and sticks are my fav
reviews.comments: This oil is so beautiful the shade Rose Amber instantly had me in a chokehold until I finally bought. I am a HUGE Fenty lover is a benchmark brand for me. But wish the applicator was made with a regular doe foot instead of the paddle shape. Also glitter chunks bother me and so probably will not repurchase. This shade is SO pretty and the lip oil lasts a good hour or so without feeling sticky. Scent is so good like a faint vanilla scent. Please add Rose Amber in the lumizer glosses!!!

reviews.headline: Didn't think I would like it but I love!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Omg! I was so excited when I opened my package! Fenty Beauty! The packaging is beautiful and I've always loved Fenty lip gloss. It's the perfect consistency. Not to sticky not to wet. It smells yummy! I was a little intimated by the color initially but once you put it on it's beautiful. It's definitely not one that I would have gravitated to but I'm glad I got to try it because it's actually beautiful. The purple shimmer is subtle but it's pops in the sun. Pair this with any brown lipliner,  and it really can be worn everyday. Love love love! 100/10

faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I recently tried the FENTY Gloss Bomb Oil in the beautiful shade Fenty Glow, and I must say, it has quickly become a staple in my makeup bag. The packaging is absolutely adorable, combining a sleek tube with a soft, rounded applicator that feels luxurious in hand. The design is simple yet chic, making it a joy to have on display.

The shine this lip oil provides is stunning. It offers a high-gloss finish that never looks overly sticky, which is a huge plus for me. The hint of glitter within the formula adds a fantastic dimension, catching the light beautifully without feeling gritty on the lips. It's the perfect balance of shine and sparkle!

Another highlight is the delightful scent‚Äîit's a sweet vanilla aroma that's not overpowering and makes application feel even more enjoyable. I find myself reaching for it just to enjoy the scent, as it brings a little joy to my day. The applicator is extremely user-friendly, allowing for precise and even application with just the right amount of product each time.

What I appreciate most about this lip oil is the quality of the ingredients. Infused with nourishing oils, it keeps my lips hydrated and soft throughout the day. I love that it's not just a pretty product but also a caring one.

The shade Fenty Glow is universally flattering, providing a sheer wash of color that enhances my natural lip tone beautifully. It pairs well with pretty much any makeup look, from everyday neutrals to more dramatic glam.

In conclusion, the FENTY Gloss Bomb Oil in Fenty Glow is a fantastic product that combines cute packaging, gorgeous shine, and nourishing ingredients. If you're looking for a lip oil that delivers on both style and substance, I highly recommend giving this one a try. It's definitely worth the hype!
faceoff_positive.headline: amazing lip oil

faceoff_negative.comments: I received the Fenty Beauty Gloss Bomb Oil in Fenty Glow complimentary for testing purposes. This is a nice lip oil but I'm a little perplexed by the choice of green shimmer for a nude gloss. It is a thinner lip oil which is fine but not my preferred texture - I prefer a thicker, plusher lip oil like Dior or elf - but it's not sticky at all which is really nice. Because it's thinner it's not super long-lasting but it is very moisturizing and layers well with additional coats, and I don't fine that I get that crusty-ness around my lips that I get with some glosses. I've liked the Fenty Glow color in their other lip products but I cannot for the life of me figure out why they would put green shimmer in this product. It gives the gloss a really yellow undertone which might work for people with darker complexions but doesn't work great for me. I'm wearing it here with the rhode lip shape in twist. Personally I will not rebuy this product because there are other lip oils I like better but I'm sure lots of people will love it!
faceoff_negative.headline: Not for me
